news.title: Indian construction equipment sales dip 1% in Q1 FY26; exports surge 34%
news.para: India's construction equipment industry experienced a slight downturn at the beginning of FY26, with sales marginally decreasing by 1%. While domestic sales saw a dip, exports surged significantly, driven by overseas demand. Industry leaders emphasize the need to accelerate infrastructure project execution to revitalize demand in the coming quarters.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills' net profit rises 2.06% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Phoenix Mills reported a 2.06% increase in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹319.91 crore in Q1 FY26. Total income grew by 4.47% to ₹984.50 crore. The retail segment saw a 12% surge in consumption, while residential sales more than tripled, highlighting strong performance across key business areas. Rajesh Kulkarni's term as a whole-time director has been extended.

news.title: Phoenix Mills to acquire CPP Investments' 49% stake in ISMDPL for ₹5,449 crore
news.para: Phoenix Mills (PML) is set to acquire CPP Investments' 49% stake in Island Star Mall Developers (ISMDPL) for ₹5,449.16 crore, gaining full ownership. The transaction, unfolding over three years, will consolidate PML's control over key retail assets like Phoenix MarketCity Bengaluru and enhance shareholder value. ISMDPL's revenue has seen substantial growth, reaching ₹919.7 crore in FY25.

news.title: IndiQube Spaces IPO fully subscribed on day 2; retail portion subscribed over seven times
news.para: IndiQube Spaces' ₹700-crore IPO was fully subscribed on its second day, driven by strong retail and non-institutional investor interest. The IPO, closing on July 25, 2025, saw an overall subscription of 2.68 times, with significant oversubscription in the retail segment. The company previously raised ₹314 crore from anchor investors, including prominent mutual funds and institutions.

news.title: Concorde to jointly develop 2.16 acres residential project in East Bengaluru
news.para: Concorde has partnered to develop Concorde Élevé, a high-rise residential project on Old Madras Road in East Bengaluru. This project, spread across 2.16 acres, features a development potential of 3.2 lakh sq ft and a gross development value of ₹475 crore.

news.title: Sri Lotus Developers' IPO to open on July 30, price band set at ₹140-₹150 per equity share
news.para: Sri Lotus Developers and Realty is launching its IPO. The price is ₹140 to ₹150 per share. The IPO opens on July 30, 2025, and closes on August 1, 2025. The IPO is a fresh issue of shares. The company has completed several projects. Revenue and profit have increased. Monarch Networth Capital and Motilal Oswal are the lead managers.

news.title: Urbanisation must focus on ease of living, not just housing: MoHUA official
news.para: D Thara emphasizes reimagining urbanization beyond housing, focusing on ease of living and balancing growth with land conservation. A whitepaper highlights the need for cyber resilience against rising threats targeting critical urban infrastructure, advocating for real-time data sharing and AI-driven response systems. Innovation and integrated urban development are crucial for India's growth.

news.title: ACC's net profit up 4.36% in Q1 FY26
news.para: ACC reported a 4.36% rise in consolidated net profit, reaching ₹375.42 crore in Q1 FY26, driven by strong cement demand and favorable macroeconomic conditions. The company's total income grew by 16.79% to ₹6,155.58 crore. ACC anticipates continued strong cement demand, projecting a 6-7% growth for FY26, fueled by housing and infrastructure investments.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's net profit increases by 21.79% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Ajmera Realty reported a 21.79% rise in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹38.28 crore in Q1 FY26, alongside a 32.36% increase in total income to ₹259.62 crore. Enhanced execution led to a 42% YoY increase in collections and the highest quarterly revenue in five years.

news.title: Don't supply power to unauthorised properties: Thane civic chief instructs electricity companies
news.para: Thane Municipal Commissioner Saurabh Rao has directed power supply companies to halt electricity provision to unauthorized structures. He emphasized the necessity of verifying the legal status of properties before supplying power, citing High Court orders.

news.title: The Supreme Industries' net profit declines 26% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Supreme Industries' Q1 FY26 profit after tax decreased to ₹202.30 crore. Net consolidated total income also saw a slight dip. However, value-added products turnover increased. The company is acquiring Wavin Industries and entering a technology license agreement. They anticipate significant cash outflow for capital expenditures and acquisitions.

news.title: EFC (I) posts net profit of ₹46.67 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: EFC (I) announced a significant surge in its financial performance for Q1 FY26, marked by a 195.94% increase in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹46.67 crore. The company's total income also saw substantial growth, rising by 112.05% to ₹223.25 crore.

news.title: Mumbai's iconic buildings' policy faces pushback from local heritage association
news.para: The Fort Heritage Conservation Association has criticized the BMC's proposed policy for 'Iconic Buildings,' deeming its definition too vague and subjective. The association, supported by other South Mumbai groups, argues that iconicity should be based on urban contribution, cultural context, and public value, not just aesthetics.

news.title: About 30,000 properties have no mention in Nagpur civic body's database, not in tax net
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation found 30,000 unrecorded properties. This discovery indicates possible tax evasion. The property tax department will cross-verify the data. Officials plan to use GIS to identify untaxed properties. The new data will capture recently constructed buildings. Ground-truthing will verify each new property. Fresh assessment notices may be issued. This could significantly boost municipal revenue for Nagpur.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM calls for future-ready Vizag master plan amid investment surge
news.para: Chief Minister N Chandrababu Naidu has directed officials to create a comprehensive master plan for Visakhapatnam, anticipating future investments and infrastructure needs. The State Investment Promotion Board approved investments worth ₹20,216 crores from Sify, Sattva, BVM, and ANSR, expected to generate 50,600 jobs.

news.title: Enlite raises ₹46 crore in series A round led by Avaana Capital
news.para: Enlite, founded in November 2017, has secured ₹46 crore in a Series A round led by Avaana Capital and Claypond Capital. The company plans to utilize the funds to expand into international markets like the Middle East and Southeast Asia, while also strengthening its presence in India.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body to roll out block level mapping and property numbering system
news.para: Prayagraj Municipal Corporation is set to implement a block-level mapping and numbering system to streamline property identification and tax collection. Each locality will be divided into blocks of approximately 100 houses, each assigned a unique identification number. This initiative aims to improve municipal services and property record management, with plans to upload records online by 2026.

news.title: Sector 53 housing scheme in Chandigarh just a nod away from launch
news.para: The Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB) is poised to launch its Sector 53 housing scheme after receiving approval from its board of directors. The proposal has been submitted to the UT administrator for final approval, with the launch expected within a month.

news.title: GMADA’s land pooling policy faces major setback in Mohali
news.para: GMADA's land pooling policy in Mohali faces significant rejection, with only 51 applications received out of nearly 8,000 eligible landowners for the proposed 2,600-acre acquisition. Farmers and political parties strongly oppose the scheme, citing concerns over inadequate compensation and potential displacement, leading to protests and demands for policy re-evaluation.
